abstract: President Trump’s aggressive use of tariffs did bring the Chinese to the negotiating table, and the United States and China signed an initial trade deal last month. But the president’s trade victory came at a high cost. His heavy use of tariffs has been painful for American consumers and businesses that are paying higher prices for products, and economists say it has weighed on the manufacturing sector that he wanted to help.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s aggressive use of tariffs did bring the Chinese to the negotiating table, and the United States and China signed an initial trade deal last month. But the president’s trade victory came at a high cost. His heavy use of tariffs has been painful for American consumers and businesses that are paying higher prices for products, and economists say it has weighed on the manufacturing sector that he wanted to help.
headline_main: “I also promised citizens I would impose tariffs to confront China’s massive theft of America’s jobs. Our strategy has worked.”

abstract: If you count President Barack Obama’s budget passed for 2017, and take into account 2018 and 2019, President Trump will have spent $2.1 trillion, as he has yet to completely spend the 2020 budget. Adjusted for inflation, both Presidents George W. Bush and Barack Obama spent more each year from 2007 through 2012, according to Breaking Defense, an industry publication.
lead_paragraph: If you count President Barack Obama’s budget passed for 2017, and take into account 2018 and 2019, President Trump will have spent $2.1 trillion, as he has yet to completely spend the 2020 budget. Adjusted for inflation, both Presidents George W. Bush and Barack Obama spent more each year from 2007 through 2012, according to Breaking Defense, an industry publication.
headline_main: “To safeguard American liberty, we have invested a record-breaking $2.2 trillion dollars in the United States military.”

abstract: Since President Trump won election in 2016, the S&P 500-stock index and the Dow Jones industrial average are each up about 60 percent.
lead_paragraph: Since President Trump won election in 2016, the S&P 500-stock index and the Dow Jones industrial average are each up about 60 percent.
headline_main: “Since my election, U.S. stock markets have soared 70 percent, adding more than $12 trillion to our nation’s wealth, transcending anything anyone believed was possible. This is a record.”

abstract: According to the Quarterly Census of Employment and Wages, the United States has added fewer than 11,000 new manufacturing establishments since President Trump took office. The bulk of those — more than 8,000 — employ five people or fewer.
lead_paragraph: According to the Quarterly Census of Employment and Wages, the United States has added fewer than 11,000 new manufacturing establishments since President Trump took office. The bulk of those — more than 8,000 — employ five people or fewer.
headline_main: “We are restoring our nation’s manufacturing might, even though predictions were that this could never be done. After losing 60,000 factories under the previous two administrations, America has now gained 12,000 new factories under my administration.”

abstract: The United States is the top producer of oil and natural gas, but it is inaccurate to credit the Trump administration or President Trump’s deregulation agenda. According to the Energy Information Administration, the United States became the world’s top oil producer in 2013 and overtook Russia as the world’s leading gas producer as far back as 2009.
lead_paragraph: The United States is the top producer of oil and natural gas, but it is inaccurate to credit the Trump administration or President Trump’s deregulation agenda. According to the Energy Information Administration, the United States became the world’s top oil producer in 2013 and overtook Russia as the world’s leading gas producer as far back as 2009.
headline_main: “Thanks to our bold regulatory reduction campaign, the United States has become the No. 1 producer of oil and natural gas anywhere in the world, by far.”

abstract: The unemployment rate under President Trump has averaged 4 percent. That is lower than even President Lyndon B. Johnson, who averaged 4.2 percent. Mr. Trump has benefited from inheriting a low unemployment rate from President Barack Obama.
lead_paragraph: The unemployment rate under President Trump has averaged 4 percent. That is lower than even President Lyndon B. Johnson, who averaged 4.2 percent. Mr. Trump has benefited from inheriting a low unemployment rate from President Barack Obama.
headline_main: “The average unemployment under my administration is lower than any administration in the history of our country.”

abstract: Prime-age participation — the share of people working or looking for work from  ages 25 to 54 —  has increased during President Trump’s tenure, climbing to 82.9 percent in December from 81.5 percent in January 2017.
lead_paragraph: Prime-age participation — the share of people working or looking for work from  ages 25 to 54 —  has increased during President Trump’s tenure, climbing to 82.9 percent in December from 81.5 percent in January 2017.

headline_main: “In eight years under the last administration, over 300,000 working-age people dropped out of the work force. In just three years of my administration, 3.5 million working-age people have joined the work force.”
headline_print_headline: “In 8 years under the last administration, over 300,000 working-age people dropped out of the workforce. In just three years of my administration, 3.5 million working-age people have joined the workforce.”

abstract: It is unclear how President Trump defines “soaring.” It is true that wages and median income have risen on Mr. Trump’s watch, as they did in the final years under President Barack Obama. But wage growth remains comparatively low for an American economy with such low unemployment, and well below the levels it enjoyed in the late 1990s.
lead_paragraph: It is unclear how President Trump defines “soaring.” It is true that wages and median income have risen on Mr. Trump’s watch, as they did in the final years under President Barack Obama. But wage growth remains comparatively low for an American economy with such low unemployment, and well below the levels it enjoyed in the late 1990s.

abstract: The two Democrats giving the official response to the State of the Union address both mentioned his impeachment, with one saying, “No one is above the law.”
snippet: The two Democrats giving the official response to the State of the Union address both mentioned his impeachment, with one saying, “No one is above the law.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats criticized President Trump on Tuesday for seeking to repeal a landmark health care law and presiding over an economy they argue has left working people struggling, in a pair of official responses to his State of the Union address that also issued a searing indictment of his conduct and language.

abstract: President Trump’s tax cuts were initially estimated at $1.5 trillion over 10 years by the Congressional Budget Office, an estimate that has since grown to around $2 trillion. But those figures are nowhere close to a record tax cut. As a share of the economy, Mr. Trump’s cuts rank around No. 8, according to Treasury Department data.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s tax cuts were initially estimated at $1.5 trillion over 10 years by the Congressional Budget Office, an estimate that has since grown to around $2 trillion. But those figures are nowhere close to a record tax cut. As a share of the economy, Mr. Trump’s cuts rank around No. 8, according to Treasury Department data.
headline_main: “From the instant I took office, I moved rapidly to revive the U.S. economy — slashing a record number of job-killing regulations, enacting historic and record-setting tax cuts …”
